<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>PSALM 50 (51) - HAVE MERCY ON ME, GOD</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em                              Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Have mercy on me, God, in your kindness.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. In your compassion blot out my offense.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. O wash me more and more from my guilt
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. and cleanse me from my sin.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. My offenses truly I know them;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. my sin is always before me.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Against you, you alone have I sinned;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. what is evil in your sight I have done.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. That you may be justified when you give sentence
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. and be without reproach when you judge.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. O see, in guilt I was born,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. a sinner was I conceived.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Indeed you love truth in the heart;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. then in the secret of my heart teach me wisdom.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. O purify me, then I shall be clean;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. O wash me, I shall be whiter than snow.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Make me hear rejoicing and gladness,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. that the bones you have crushed may revive.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. From my sins turn away your face
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. and blot out all my guilt.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. A pure heart create for me, O God,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. put a steadfast spirit within me.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Do not cast me away from your presence,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. nor deprive me of your holy spirit.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Give me again the joy of your help;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. with a spirit of fervor sustain me,

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. that I may teach transgressors your ways
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. and sinners may return to you.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. O rescue me, God, my helper
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. and my tounge shall ring out your goodness.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. O Lord, open my lips
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. and my mouth shall declare your praise.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. For in sacrifice you take no delight,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. burnt offering from me you would refuse,

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. my sacrifice, a contrite spirit.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. A humbled, contrite heart you will not spurn.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. In your goodness, show favor to Zion:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Then you will be pleased with lawful sacrifice,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. holocausts offered on your altar.



</H3></PRE>
